From the experiences I have had, there have been no SoL boss encounters that have not required the use of mod rods to help kill the boss mob. I probably sound crazy but I enjoy making massive piles of rods..during big encounters our guild's mage team does an awesome job of making sure there are rods for everyone including nukers.. Juggling rods is not a new idea..i never realised how effective it can be though until I joined Mythic Legion (thanks guys you all rule) It is fun to see how many rods you can get on the ground before the mob is engaged (most so far was around 100 for burrower parasite). Anyway..another thing which may need to be added is some mages who begrudge non clerics who use the rods during fights too. Wizards create awesome DPS with rod/epic rune combo and druids/shammies keep spot heals on rodding mages and clerics so everyone plays their part..Those extra few bars of mana a wizard uses nuking could be the difference between victory or a CR If there is a shortage of rods due to this..you should be making more rods! I love the new spell (well not so new anymore) It was worth every penny of the 10kpp that I paid for it (when luclin was new). When i'm there making rods providing mana for clerics to keep the tanks alive I feel part of the team and needed..if providing rods is not something you enjoy doing, maybe you should consider another class because, like it or no, Magicians are the vending machines of EQ and in a end game situation you shouldnt be doing anything else unless damage shielding :P<br>
Soloing still involves a fair bit of down time but rodding between fights helps especially with regen 3 and tpp. I am hoping to one day get one of those lovely rune shields then i'll be able to die happy :P. Keep on rodding people <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
