Perhaps if you had not given such a <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>cursory</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> examination of the argument and the spells involved, you could have easily derived this yourself.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> In the other thread it doesnt take rodding into account so again is rodding in combination with bind and self regen more efficent or comparable to just sitting down?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->What other thread?<br>
<br>
In <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showMessage?topicID=136.topic">2nd Basic Skill: Regeneration or First Aid?</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, I analyze this exact subject, and conclude that self-bandaging after transvergence is a simply awful idea compared to sitting down and meditating.  The more recent thread <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showMessage?topicID=242.topic">AA Re-gen vs Bind Wound (help)</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> contains a link to the former thread, so I did not feel the need to repeat the analysis in the latter.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I dont see how someone who likes to analyze things can just brush that off seeing as your thread is about trods.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Perhaps the only thing I missed is the possibility of others bandaging the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> while he meditates.  I will be sure to add that as soon as I have the numbers in hand.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Not an insult just curious.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Are you sure it is not intended as an insult?  You call my work <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;cursory&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> when it is the product hours of calculutions, references, and reviews, contains links to the spell definitions, summarizes the best knowledge on the effects of specialization and spell casting mastery, and is based on specific facts and cases.  Then you accuse me of omitting analysis which is already there, and ignoring things that in fact make no difference, and hence should be ignored.<br>
<br>
Perhaps you would be better served by something more than a cursory reading.<br>
<br>
